comment: This lemma proves the existence of a function p as in the proof of Lemma 1 in [BrosowskiDeutsh] p. 90: p is in the subalgebra, such that 0 <= p <= 1, p_(t_0) = 0, and p > 0 on T - U. Here Z is used to represent t_0 in the paper. (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 20-Apr-2017.)
